WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. It's Sunday, March 29th, 2026. Let's get

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
into your daily briefing. Opening with weather. Jefferson City: 73

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
degrees and partly sunny today with just 2 percent chance

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
of rain. Tomorrow jumps to 87 and sunny. Missouri is

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
apparently apologizing for that 93-degree atrocity last week by giving

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
you a perfect Sunday. Over in Tacoma: 49 degrees with

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
light rain likely, 70 percent chance of precipitation. Classic Pacific

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Northwest spring. Monday clears up to 50 and sunny. Your

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
calendar. Today is wide open except for a Read Scan

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Reports block from 10 to 11 A-M on your work

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
calendar. Tomorrow, Ben arrives in Jeff City to help with

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
the carpet. Tuesday is payday and the carpet install runs

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
from 9 A-M to 2 P-M. Wednesday is a big

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
one: Q-2 starts, Apple turns 50, and Karen announces her

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
retirement at 11 A-M with hiring projects starting immediately after.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Thursday is your triple-header: the Anthropic pilot discussion at 9

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
A-M, Bill Review Training for Departments at 2 P-M, and

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
dinner with Alex, Chris, and Dustin at 6 P-M. Oh,

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
and Thursday is also the government's deadline to appeal the

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Anthropic ruling. It's Katelyn's off day too. Plan accordingly. Now

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
to your text messages. Katelyn spent Saturday doing extreme cleaning

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
and yardwork, then headed to Trader Joe's. She apologized for

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
being less responsive. The big update: she bought something fun

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
at Ace Hardware, which appears to be a crow-feeding setup.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
She sent photos. Jacob called it her first cult meeting

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
and joked that risotto's proximity might be counterproductive. Turkey vultures

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
were discussed. She asked where to put the feeder; Jacob

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
suggested the kitchen window. Jacob also told Katelyn about the

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
daily briefing system, the Reddit tool integration, and the auto-generated

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
podcast feed. He shared a Rivian article about them winning

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
a dealer law fight in Washington. And there was a

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
Haim-related YouTube short exchange. Ben's thread was mostly about the

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
Claude briefing system. Jacob told him quote, This morning I

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
had Claude create an audio version of a daily briefing

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
that reads my emails, texts, news, etc. And then it

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
also made a podcast feed. I feel like the world

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
is changing kinda fast, end quote. They also discussed settling

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
up on the dinner split, about 237 dollars. The group

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
chat with Dustin and Alex has been quiet since Friday

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
night. The no-parking-sign victory and the Crossley loss remain the

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
last topics. Alex shared The Verge's Apple 50th anniversary ranking

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
tool and discussed AirPods Max 2, considering them for Chris

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
since the purple matches their iPad Air. And your 618

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
Capitol contact sent a notable message Saturday: quote, I can't

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
believe we're losing budget, daddy, end quote. This is either

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
a term of endearment or a cry for help. Either

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
way, it's the first work-relevant text from this contact in

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
several briefings. Identify them at Thursday dinner. Moving to the

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
big stories. The Iran war enters Day 30 with a

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
massive escalation signal. The Washington Post reports the Pentagon is

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
preparing for weeks of ground operations in Iran, including raids

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
on Kharg Island, Iran's primary oil export terminal, and coastal

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
sites near the Strait of Hormuz. The 82nd Airborne Division

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
has been directed to deploy with several thousand troops. Up

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
to 10,000 additional combat troops are being considered. The White

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
House says no final decision has been made. Other Iran

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
developments: Russia took satellite images of the U-S airbase at

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
Prince Sultan in Saudi Arabia before Iran's attack that wounded

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
15-plus service members. Zelenskyy revealed this, and the intelligence-sharing implication

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
is damning. A key U-S Air Force E-3 AWACS early

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
warning aircraft was damaged in the Iranian attack. Only about

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
30 of these exist worldwide. The Guardian reports the U-S

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
has destroyed only about a third of Iran's missile arsenal

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
after 30 days of strikes. And 3,500 Marines arrived in

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
the region aboard the U-S-S Tripoli. Thousands protested across Israel

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
calling to end the war. Oil is at 112 dollars

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
and 57 cents a barrel for Brent crude, the highest

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
since July 2022. The D-H-S shutdown reaches Day 44 with

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
Congress on a two-week recess. Trump signed a presidential memorandum

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
to restart T-S-A pay, with paychecks expected as early as

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
Monday. The legal authority is contested, but the practical effect

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
is that 61,000-plus workers who missed three paychecks should see

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
money this week. No resolution to the shutdown is possible

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
before mid-April. Quick status board. The Anthropic versus Pentagon case:

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
Judge Lin's preliminary injunction holds. The government's appeal deadline is

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
Thursday, same day as your pilot discussion. The Anthropic Mythos

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
leak continues reverberating: a new model tier above Opus, cybersecurity

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
stocks dropped 7 percent, and Claude's paid subscribers have more

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
than doubled this year according to TechCrunch. Apple turns 50

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
on Wednesday with global retail celebrations already underway. Tim Cook

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
published a "50 Years of Thinking Different" letter. W-W-D-C is

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
June 8th, 71 days away. Tech and Apple roundup. Apple

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
is releasing two entirely new iPhone apps this year. More

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
U-S states plan to support digital driver's licenses in Apple

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Wallet. The MacBook Neo with A-18 Pro chip is surprisingly

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
capable for gaming. The iPhone Air's C-1-X modem matches Qualcomm

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
on speed and wins on latency. Apple's A-I Playlist Playground

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
is still bad at music. Lockdown Mode remains undefeated, with

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
no iPhone ever successfully hacked while running it. And from

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
The Verge's Installer newsletter: Flighty is the must-have app for

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
navigating T-S-A chaos, there's a new Riz Ahmed James Bond

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
meta-show called Bait, and Notion 3.4 got some genuinely nice

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
non-A-I updates. From Reddit: the White House's official app is

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
tracking users' G-P-S location every 4.5 minutes via a third-party

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
server. The White House unveiled "Only Farms," a website for

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
farmers with a golden tractor on the South Lawn. In

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
Tacoma, No Kings protests happened at Point Defiance and Wright

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
Park, though one poster said the Wright Park event lacked

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
urgency. A Hyundai owner had their car broken into but

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
the steering wheel lock saved it, and a kind stranger

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
left a note on their windshield. Jobs update. The City

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
of Seattle Economics and Revenue Analyst is now on Day

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
12. It pays 118 to 177 thousand dollars. Apply this

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
week if you're going to. The Anthropic careers page confirms

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
all three watchlist roles are still posted: Analyst at the

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
Anthropic Institute, Communications Manager for Research, and Geopolitics Analyst. New

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
finds include three Solutions Architect roles for national security, government

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
technology, and federal civilian, all in D-C and New York.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
And King County has a Deputy Division Director role at

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
173 to 219 thousand. Action items. Prep for the Anthropic

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
pilot meeting Thursday. Review the Claude pilot explainer note in

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
Apple Notes. Apply for the City of Seattle role this

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
week. Renew your GitHub token, which has been expired since

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:36.000
March 26th. Coordinate carpet logistics with Ben. And respond to

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.000
Katelyn about July time off, she's still waiting. Closing thoughts.

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.000
Today's briefing is brought to you by the Pentagon, which

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
is simultaneously preparing for a ground war in Iran, losing

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:52.000
AWACS planes, discovering Russia is providing satellite targeting data to

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
the enemy, and getting its plans leaked to the Washington

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
Post. A level of multitasking that makes this daily briefing

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
look like a grocery list. The White House named its

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
farmer outreach website "Only Farms," which means someone in a

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
federal building typed that into a domain registrar with a

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
straight face. Katelyn is building a crow-feeding station. Jacob called

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
it her first cult meeting. Befriending the crows of Tacoma

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
may be the most strategically sound decision anyone in this

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.000
briefing is making. At least the crows won't leak your

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
plans to the Washington Post. It's 73 degrees and gorgeous

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
in Jefferson City. Go outside. The crows will wait. Happy

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:36.400
Sunday.
